# i18n Usage

## Rules

- **All user-facing text must use `useTranslation()`.** Every string visible to users (labels, messages, placeholders, tooltips, error messages, toast notifications) must come from translation files via the `t()` function.
- **Use flat 3-level dot notation for keys.** Translation keys follow the pattern: `<module>.<section>.<key>`. Examples: `auth.login.title`, `dashboard.stats.total_users`, `common.actions.save`.
- **Module-based organization.** Translation files are organized by module. Each module has its own namespace or section in the translation JSON.
- **Never hardcode English text in JSX.** Not even "OK", "Cancel", "Loading...", or single words. These must all go through i18n.
- **Use interpolation for dynamic values.** Use `t('users.greeting', { name: user.name })` with `{{name}}` in the translation file. Never concatenate strings.
- **Use pluralization support.** Use `t('items.count', { count })` with `_one`, `_other` suffixes in translation files.
- **Keep keys descriptive but concise.** Keys should clearly indicate what the string is: `auth.login.submit_button`, not `auth.btn1`.
- **Use the `common` namespace** for shared strings like "Save", "Cancel", "Delete", "Loading", "Error" that appear across modules.
- **Translation files use JSON format** and are located in `src/locales/<lang>/`.

## Examples

### Good

```typescript
// Component with proper i18n
import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';

export const LoginForm = () => {
  const { t } = useTranslation();

  return (
    <Card>
      <CardHeader>
        <CardTitle>{t('auth.login.title')}</CardTitle>
        <CardDescription>{t('auth.login.subtitle')}</CardDescription>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <Input placeholder={t('auth.login.email_placeholder')} />
        <Input placeholder={t('auth.login.password_placeholder')} />
        <Button type="submit">{t('auth.login.submit_button')}</Button>
        <p>{t('auth.login.forgot_password')}</p>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  );
};

// Interpolation
t('users.greeting', { name: user.name })
// Translation: "Welcome back, {{name}}"

// Pluralization
t('items.count', { count: items.length })
// Translation: { "items": { "count_one": "{{count}} item", "count_other": "{{count}} items" } }

// Toast with i18n
toast.success(t('users.create_success'));
toast.error(t('errors.generic'));

// Zod error messages as i18n keys
z.string().min(1, { message: 'validation.required' })
```

```json
// src/locales/en/translation.json
{
  "common": {
    "actions": {
      "save": "Save",
      "cancel": "Cancel",
      "delete": "Delete",
      "edit": "Edit",
      "confirm": "Confirm"
    },
    "status": {
      "loading": "Loading...",
      "error": "An error occurred",
      "empty": "No results found"
    }
  },
  "auth": {
    "login": {
      "title": "Sign In",
      "subtitle": "Enter your credentials to continue",
      "email_placeholder": "Email address",
      "password_placeholder": "Password",
      "submit_button": "Sign In",
      "forgot_password": "Forgot your password?"
    }
  }
}
```

### Bad

```typescript
// Hardcoded English text
<Button>Save</Button>
<p>Loading...</p>
<span>No results found</span>
<Input placeholder="Enter your email" />
toast.error('Failed to save changes');

// String concatenation instead of interpolation
<p>{t('users.greeting') + ' ' + user.name}</p>
<p>{`Welcome, ${user.name}`}</p>

// Deeply nested keys (more than 3 levels)
t('modules.auth.pages.login.form.fields.email.placeholder')

// Non-descriptive keys
t('auth.str1')
t('common.btn2')
t('page.text')
```
